In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the mixture, alternating
with corn tortillas. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Good!

title: date orange toppers
directions: In a saucepan, combine dates, water and sugar.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until it thickens.
Remove from heat. Add nuts.
Slice cookie dough into 36 slices (thin).
Place 27 cookies on cookie sheet.
Place 1 tablespoon of date nut mixture on top of each slice.
Cut remaining 9 slices into thirds.
Place each third onto date top mixture.
Sprinkle with orange peel.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly golden.
Cool and serve. Makes 27 cookies.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Place all
ingredients	in
blender.
Blend for 20 seconds. Pour into glass and serve.	Enjoy!!!

title: macaroni and beef skillet dinner
directions: Cook the noodles.
Drain and set aside.
Saute the meat, onions and garlic in oil until the meat loses its pink color and the onions are tender.
Add pepper, tomato sauce, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring mixture to a boil, then simmer gently about 5 minutes.
Mix in the cooked macaroni and simmer for 5 more minutes.

title: orange pineapple smoothie
directions: Blend orange juice, pineapple and orange rind in a blender for 20 seconds.
Add ice cream and blend 10 seconds more.
Makes 2 drinks.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water and dissolve the jello; cool.
Add the strawberries and pineapple. Refrigerate until firm in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with mixture of cream cheese and whipped cream. Cut into squares to serve.

title: poulet saute au vin blanc
directions: Dry chicken joints.
Heat butter and oil in wide pan with cover and saute chicken briskly.
Season, cover pan and cook over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add shallots or onions to pan, cook 1 minute.
Add wine and boil rapidly, stirring occasionally until reduced to half.
Stir in cream, replace chicken and simmer until sauce thickens slightly.
Serve with buttered rice or wild rice.
May be made ahead, but add cream and wine at last minute.

title: juicy salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; pack in a well greased loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for 35 minutes or until firm and light brown on top.
Loosen sides of loaf with knife; let stand in pan 5 minutes.
Slice.
Serves 4.

title: creamy celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Yields about 1 cup.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix well with wooden spoon.
Let stand at room temperature for 6 to 8 hours.

title: party dessert
directions: Crust:
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and cook the egg yolks, sugar and crushed pineapple until thick.
Add lemon Jell-O (no water); add the 8 egg whites and fold into pineapple mixture after it has cooled.
Make 24 hours before serving.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Add milk to creamed mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Fill vanilla fluff between two cookies when cooled.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pink party punch
directions: Dilute lemonade as directed on can.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into plastic container and freeze.
Take out several hours before serving.
Pour ginger ale mixture, making slush color to choice.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese in small mixing bowl on high speed of mixer until almost smooth, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, coconut, honey, orange peel and vanilla.
Chill, covered 2 to 3 hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with fresh fruit of season.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: skip a step rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Place shortening, sugar and salt in mixing bowl, add boiling water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir in eggs and flour. Shape into rolls or doughnuts.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° until brown or deep fat fry.

title: sauerkraut spareribs
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces.
In a large bowl, combine half of the green onion, the minced garlic, vinegar, soy sauce, the first tablespoon oil and the red and black peppers.
Add the chicken pieces; stir to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: dog chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in a large pan.
Add the cereal and coat thoroughly.
Place in a large paper bag with the powdered sugar and toss.

title: greek spanakopita recipe
directions: Squeeze remaining liquid from spinach and place in large bowl, tear into small pieces.
Beat eggs, crumble feta cheese and add to spinach.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until brown, add to spinach, season with pepper and oregano.
Butter a large oblong baking dish.

title: pollo magnifico(pibil)
directions: Place chicken pieces between 2 slices of wax paper and pound with mallet until 1/4 inch thick. In large Ziploc bag, combine all ingredients together. Seal bag, squeezing out air; turn to coat chicken. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight, turning bag occasionally.

title: chicken with raspberry vinegar
directions: Lightly sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat a 4 or 6-quart pressure cooker; add oil and brown chicken breasts.
Add shallots, chicken broth and vinegar.
Close cover securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook for 3 minutes at 15 pounds pressure with pressure regular rocking slowly.
Cool cooker at once.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Return to pan to heat and bring liquid to a boil.
Stir in rice; remove pan from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in raspberries.
Serve with chicken. Yield: 4 servings.

title: old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes on 350°.

title: honey-lime and mustard chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Combine honey (2 tablespoons), mustard and lime juice.
Pour over chicken and marinade at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Cook rice according to package directions, adding peas, pepper strips and 1 tablespoon honey after rice has simmered 22 minutes.
Remove chicken from marinade.

title: advent christian punch
directions: Mix all together and add the lime or pineapple sherbet when ready to serve.
Serves 50.

title: apple betty
directions: Peel apples and slice.
Mound them in buttered 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with the orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine.
Sprinkle this mixture over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with salt.
Add marshmallow cream and mix. Put on favorite pie.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Place in microwave for 1 minute on High.
Stir and repeat for another minute.
Stir in vanilla. Put aside and let cool.

title: orange pecan thins
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 c. sugar in small bowl.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour to mixture along with grated rind.	Mix. Spread mixture evenly over a 10 x 15 jelly roll pan.
Beat egg white until foamy and then gradually add 1/4 c. sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over base, sprinkle nuts on top.	Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed chicken
directions: In thickest side of each chicken piece, cut a pocket large enough for cheese.
Place a cheese slice in each pocket.
Beat together egg, Parmesan cheese, parsley, bouillon and dash of pepper.
Coat chicken with flour and dip in egg mixture.
Brown in hot oil 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Transfer to 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: herbed lentil casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a 3-quart ungreased casserole.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until moist, not runny.
If using cheese, add to top and bake an extra 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Combine next three (chips, water and oatmeal) in a bowl and let set for 10 minutes. Sift together flour, baking soda and cocoa; add to egg and sugar mixture.
Finally, add oatmeal mix to the previous mixture and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; top with remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hearty chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, then strain off grease.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush up cookies with a rolling pin.
Pour melted butter over cookie crumbs.
Press half of crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Reserve remaining crumbs for topping.
Beat 1 1/2 cups milk with cream cheese until mixture is fluffy.
Add pudding and remaining milk and mix well.
Fold whipped topping into pudding mixture.
Spread pudding mixture over cookie crumbs.
Spread reserved crumbs over pudding layers.
Chill and serve.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let it set until it starts to congeal. Soften cream cheese and mix with whipped cream; fold with other ingredients into gelatin. Pour into mold and chill. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: microwave munchies
directions: Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High (glass pan).
Stir in seasoning. Mix with rest of ingredients.
Microwave 2 to 4 minutes on High.
Makes 7 cups.

title: microwave rice
directions: In a casserole dish, cook on High for 5 minutes, then on 1/2 power for 25 minutes.

title: chinese salad
directions: Crush Top Ramen with rolling pin and toss together with above ingredients.

title: fruit 'n pudding crisp
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole or 8-inch square baking pan; set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients in large bowl until well blended and crumbly.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° (325° glass) for 40 to 45 minutes until deep golden brown and bubbly.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: sugar-free raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and apples in water for 3 minutes.
Add shortening to melt.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients with nuts last; mix well.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Refrigerate cookies.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, syrup, salt and flavoring.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn; mix well.
Scatter in large shallow pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: corn fritters(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, milk and corn.
Add dash of salt and pepper.
Blend well beaten egg and add.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into hot fat and fry a golden brown.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook until it forms a real soft ball in cold water.
Add the coconut; cook until 240°, or until it forms a soft ball.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Let cool until bottom of pan is warm.
Beat with electric mixer (add a few drops of red coloring if pink color is desired) until it begins to hold its shape when dropped from spoon.
Drop onto wax paper; top with pecan halves or pieces.
Store in tins.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill over night.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Combine soup and water.
Measure out 1/2 cup soup mixture and combine with bread crumbs, ground beef, onions, egg and salt. Shape into meat balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Brown meatballs in a large skillet, using 1 tablespoon oil.
Add remaining soup mixture, cover and cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
You may shape into patties if you prefer.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, sugar, oil and eggs for 4 minutes. Pour half of batter in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle more than 1/2 of mixture over batter.
Add remainder of batter and sprinkle rest of mixture over this.
Cut across a few times with knife to mix.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes or more.
Ice.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, refried beans and salsa; top with cheese. Heat in microwave for about 3 to 4 minutes, or until cheese melts. Dip with nachos.
It's wonderful!

title: carrot pineapple salad
directions: Grate or shred the carrots.
Drain the pineapple.
Boil ginger ale. Pour over lemon jello.
Mix.
Add carrots and pineapple. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
May be topped with Miracle Whip/pineapple dressing.
Make the day before if desired.

title: feta spinach and fruit salad with honey-lemon dressing
directions: Place spinach, fruit, onion, cheese and olives in large bowl. Toss lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients; add and toss.
Makes 6 cups or 6 side-salad servings.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Add sherbet (which has just been removed from the freezer) and
stir until sherbet is completely blended with the gelatin. Pour mixture into a 2-quart mold and spread sour cream over the top. Chill for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add soda, baking powder and salt; sift again.
Cream shortening and peanut butter; gradually add the sugars and cream thoroughly.
Add well beaten egg.
Combine the dry ingredients and creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Form into balls 1-inch in diameter and place on a lightly greased and floured baking sheet.
Flatten with fork making crisscross pattern.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Pour half of batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan (10-inch).
Combine sugar, cinnamon and finely chopped nuts and sprinkle half this mixture onto batter.
Pour in the remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining sugar, cinnamon and nut mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: batter fried vegetables
directions: In a bowl, stir together cornstarch, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in water and egg until smooth.
Pour corn oil into a large skillet at depth of 1/2 inch, filling skillet no more than 1/3 full.
Heat oil over medium heat to 375°.
Dip vegetables, a few at a time, into batter (stir batter occasionally).
Carefully add vegetables to hot oil a few pieces at a time.
Fry, turning once, for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.
Drain.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt butter; add peanut butter and sugar and mix well.
Add crumbs and mix.
Spread in buttered pan (I use a 9 x 13 pan). Melt the chocolate chips over hot water and spread on top of peanut butter mixture.

title: blonde brownies
directions: In a large bowl, mix brown sugar, eggs and butter. Mix well with a wooden spoon. Then add in flour, baking powder, soda, pecans and vanilla. Mix well and pour into a greased baking pan. Spread in pan and sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips over batter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (center will be soft).

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels (use a Ziploc bag).
Put pretzels in a bowl. Add margarine and sugar.
Mix well with a fork and place in a 9 x 13 dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Beat together softened cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries. Refrigerate until partially set.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crust.
Add Jell-O with berries and refrigerate.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Break
the
lettuce
into
bite size pieces.
Layer the ingredients in a 9
x 11-inch Pyrex dish as follows:
lettuce, onion, celery, bell
pepper
and peas.
Combine the mayonnaise and sugar; spread
on top.
Cover this with cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cole slaw healthy eating
directions: Whip mayo, mustard, Equal, vinegar, oil and milk with a wire whip. Pour over cabbage and carrots. Toss until well coated. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well and add the pumpkin, oil and water.
Blend well.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Divide into 3 greased and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great served warm or cold.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Pour into an ice cream freezer and fill with milk.
Freeze.

title: easy streusel pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 375°.
In large bowl, using a wire whisk, whisk together the eggs, pumpkin, milk, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons spice.
Pour filling into 1 frozen crust.
Bake on preheated baking sheet for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O; cool.
Put peaches in pie shell.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Refrigerate to jell.

title: "tennessee" dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half in 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass cake pan. In a medium mixing bowl, mix milk, pudding and vanilla; let stand. In another bowl, cream the butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Combine the mixtures and pour over the crumbs in the pan.
Top with other half of Oreo crumbs.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: easy does it meat pie
directions: Defrost 2 pie shells.
Cover meat with water in frying pan. Cook until brown.
Drain all water off meat.
Add 1 can or jar gravy; brown with onions.
Do not add water into gravy.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with the other pie shell.
Brush top with 1 egg. Put 4 or 5 slits on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Skin chicken before cooking.
Boil chicken and let cool. Debone chicken.
Add other ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.

title: grandma's mac and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Place in 2 1/2 qt. greased casserole dish.
Melt butter over medium heat, stir in flour; mix well.
Add milk and cook over medium heat, stir constantly until sauce thickens.
Add salt, sugar, and cheese, mix well.
Mix sour cream and cheese into sauce.
Pour over macaroni; mix well.
Sprinkle grated cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Dot with butter.
The dish may be frozen at this point.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: strawberry satin pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt in saucepan.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook
until very thick and bubbling. Stir a little of hot mixture into
egg.
Add
egg to hot mixture; cook, then chill thoroughly.
(Mixture will be very thick.) Beat until smooth and velvety.
Whip cream and
fold
into filling mixture.
Add vanilla. Fill
shell.
Refrigerate until serving
time.
Add
thickened
strawberries on top.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: First layer shredded lettuce.
Second layer coarsely chopped celery.
Third layer coarsely chopped green pepper.
Fourth layer Spanish onion, separated into rings.
Fifth layer the sugar peas that have been drained.
Sixth layer spread mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle sugar on mayonnaise.
Seventh layer shredded cheese.
May sprinkle bacon crumbs on top.

title: veal goulash
directions: Dredge veal with paprika; set aside.
Heat oil in Dutch oven. Add chopped onions and saute until lightly browned.
Remove onions using slotted spoon and set aside.
Brown dredged veal on all sides.
Return onions to Dutch oven.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and salt.
Simmer gently, uncovered, about 1 hour or until veal is tender.
Serve over noodles.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: a whole meal in a baked potato
directions: Scrub potatoes; dry
and
place
on
racks in 450° oven. Bake until tender (approximately 1 hour).
Cook vegetables in a medium saucepan
until
tender
to
taste.
Place vegetables in bowl. Measure cooking
liquid,
then
add milk to make 2 cups. Pour into saucepan
and set over medium heat.
Toss cheese with flour. Gradually
add to hot liquid, stirring constantly until cheese melts and
sauce is smooth.
Stir in vegetables.
Cover; keep warm.
When
potatoes
are
tender, immediately cut crisscross tops to release steam.
Squeeze
and
press
ends
toward center to fluff up insides.
Place
on
serving
dishes and top each with sauce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add ingredients, one by one.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes, then at 350° until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop by spoons into hot grease and brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and
drain
meat.
Combine other ingredients with meat and
simmer until thick.
Serve over toasted or untoasted hamburger buns.

title: wylene's potato bacon chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Saute onion in a little bacon grease.
Remove onion and drain.
Cook potatoes in 2 cups water.
When cooked, add all ingredients and simmer.
(Do not boil.)

title: tuna spread
directions: Beat all ingredients, except tuna, with mixer.
Stir in tuna. Refrigerate.
Serve with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large roasting pan, combine soups and wine.
Add beef.
Cover tightly and bake three hours.
Add noodles.
Cover and bake one hour.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato bake(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cut pineapple chunks in half.
Combine pineapple
with juice, potatoes, salt and butter.
Place half of mixture in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with half of the marshmallows.
Add remaining half of potato mixture.
Arrange pecans on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover about 10 minutes before serving.
Add remaining marshmallows.

title: crepes suzettes(thin pancakes)
directions: Beat together eggs, salt, sugar, milk and flour until smooth. Heat frying pan.
Brush bottom with butter or oil.
Pour in a thin layer of batter.
Spread by tilting pan.
Pancakes must be very thin (almost transparent).
Fry on both sides to a golden brown.
Spread with jelly or cheese.
Roll up and keep warm until served.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Can be kept warm at 200°.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding; sprinkle over rolls.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over all this and pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on cabinet overnight to rise; do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn over and dump on plate to serve.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Crush some vanilla wafers and place crushed wafers in a pie plate.
Stand up vanilla wafers around plate.
Mix together separated eggs (save whites for frosting), milk and lemon juice. Mix. Place in pie crust.
Mix egg whites and 1/3 cup sugar for meringue.
Place in oven and let brown.

title: chicken skillet stew
directions: Cut
chicken in serving pieces; roll in flour, salt and paprika.
Brown
in
butter;
push
to
side
of skillet.
Add potatoes and
carrot;
pour
soup
over
all.
Cover;
cook on simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
When done, take up and
put on serving platter, leaving drippings in pan.
Add sour cream
to
drippings, mix until heated through.
Serve at once with rolls (or corn sticks) and salad.

title: south of the border
directions: Line bottom of a 5-quart casserole with half the corn chips. Layer the remaining ingredients in the following order: onion, kidney beans, olives, burger and remaining chips.
In a small mixing bowl, combine tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Pour the sauce over the top of the layered mixture.
Put cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake in three greased and floured cake pans. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form center.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place basil, pine nuts, garlic and cheese in the work bowl of a food processor and process until a near-puree is obtained.
Pour oil slowly through the feed tube while the motor runs and scrap down the sides of the work bowl with a rubber spatula once or twice.
Run 20 to 30 seconds longer.
Remove and reserve.
Makes approximately 1/2 cup.
This may be frozen. Can be served over pasta and used with seafood and chicken dishes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmons, sugar, eggs and flour with soda, salt and spices.
Using electric mixer, stir in milk and melted butter. Add vanilla.
Put mixture into a greased baking dish and bake in moderate oven at 350°, but we have always found 325° to work better.
It will take approximately 1 hour, depending upon depth of pan.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning with refried beans.
Spread mixture into a baking dish suitable for serving.
Spread sour cream on top of the beans.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top of the sour cream. Bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
When cooked and cooled, cube and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.

title: sour cream beets
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Carefully stir in beets. Heat slowly, stirring often.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: microwave islander chicken
directions: Cut
larger pieces of chicken in half for uniform size. Arrange, skin side up, in 2 quart baking dish.
Combine juice, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and lime juice.
Pour over chicken. Cook,
covered
with wax paper, 28 minutes or until chicken is done,
spooning sauce over chicken during last half of cooking time.
Add bananas and nuts.
Cook, uncovered, 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Spread bread crumbs and slivered almonds on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza
directions: First, you make the dough and toss it up and down.
Then, you put all the ingredients.
You put it in the oven, then you will have a pizza.

title: carol spack's crisp green salad
directions: This salad is very refreshing on a hot summer night.
I prefer to use organic vegetables, particularly lettuce, which has a sweeter and more distinctive taste.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Prepare 1/2 recipe of dough.
Shape as desired.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake about 20 minutes on greased baking sheet.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: old-time tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: no-process mustard pickles
directions: Mix and pour over washed pickling cukes in jars.
Open and enjoy after 3 weeks.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a large grocery bag.
Combine oleo, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in a large glass pitcher.
Bring to boil on Full Power.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn in bag.
Close bag and shake vigorously.
Place bag in microwave.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake again.
Return to oven for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake again.
Return to oven for 1 minute.
Remove and pour on cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes with salt, sugar and oleo.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in pecans.
Arrange in shallow baking dish. Make a dent in ball with thumb.
Place a marshmallow in dent. Bake at 300° until marshmallow is melted and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy and stir in Cool Whip.
Add food color.
In a bowl, mix pineapple, fruit cocktail, cherries, mandarin oranges, marshmallows and nuts.
Add ingredients and mix.
Makes large bowl.

title: veggie meat loaf
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all the ingredients together, using hands.
After thoroughly mixed, shape into loaf and press into 4 x 10-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, pouring off grease as it surfaces.
Let cool 5 minutes after removing from pan.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Quickly heat tortillas in hot oil.
On each tortilla, layer 2 tablespoons of chicken, 1 teaspoon onion, 1 teaspoon olives, 1 tablespoon sour cream and 1 tablespoon cheese. Roll up each tortilla and place in oblong baking dish.

title: asparagus mold
directions: * Broccoli may be used in place of asparagus, steam before using.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
cracker
crumbs and margarine. Stir crumbs into margarine	and
sprinkle on top of the other ingredients.
Bake in 2 quart
dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbles.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl for about 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve coffee powder in hot water.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with coffee and buttermilk, beating just until blended after each addition. Pour into well-greased and floured, fluted tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended after each addition.
Add vanilla, beating until blended.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars until fluffy. Add in the eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the dry ingredients and slowly add. Lastly, mix in the oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut. Drop from teaspoon 3 to 4-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg and parsley. Shape into meat balls.
In skillet, brown meat balls.
Pour off drippings. Stir in soup and 1/2 can of water (or milk).
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Stir often.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In resealable plastic bag, combine chicken, buttermilk, thyme, pepper sauce and refrigerate for 1 hour. Remove chicken.
In separate resealable plastic bag, combine chicken and croutons; shake to coat.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake 30 minutes turning once.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Mix together and pour batter into cupcake papers.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: my favorite butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cornstarch together with dash of salt. Add milk; stir well until sugar is dissolved. Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly. Add part of mixture (several spoonfuls) to beaten egg yolks. Add back to remaining mixture and cook, covered, until thick (about 15 minutes), stirring occasionally, until cool. Top with Dream Whip topping. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 4 ingredients. Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in water until tender; drain.
Layer in baking dish using noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa-buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with the vanilla.
Gradually add the sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add cocoa, soda and salt.
Turn mixer on low speed.
Add buttermilk slowly and flour.
This makes three 9-inch layers or one 9 x 13-inch pan cake.
Ice with your favorite frosting.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add fruit and just a little of the juice. Fold in Cool Whip and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix dressing with butter.
Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of dressing mix.
Put in casserole and top with balance of dressing. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and green pepper in skillet and drain.
Add all ingredients in crock-pot and simmer for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Use greased 9 x 13-inch pan and dump first 2 ingredients in. Spread out but don't mix.
Shake cake mix over all.
Slice 2 sticks margarine on top, then coconut and nuts.
Bake until done, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: hominy pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions add brown lightly.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Blend well.
Add flour and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in hominy.
Pour into 7 x 12 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese melts.

title: easiest souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bring mixture to room temperature before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until is firmly set.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cocoa. Add eggs. Blend in flour. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool to warm. Spread marshmallow cream over cake.
Cool.
Frost cake.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add spices.
Stir in corn syrup.
Add eggs one at a time, stirring after each addition until blended.
Stir in oats.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean. During baking the oatmeal forms a chewy crust on top.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Add hot dogs.
Simmer on stove 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans and put in kettle.
Add 2 1/2 quarts of water and bring to boil.
Boil, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, for 2 hours or until beans are mushy.
Remove bay leaves and ham bone.
Remove any meat from bone and put back in soup.
Season to taste and if necessary, thicken with flour-water paste.
Makes about 2 1/2-quarts.
Can substitute with ham shanks.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add coconut. Beat egg whites until they are stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into 4 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
Mix soup and soy sauce in bowl.
Place all in baking dish.
Cover with soy sauce. Place shredded cheese on top of mixture. Top with 6 to 8 slices of french bread.
Then place 6 to 8 slices of swiss cheese on top of bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375 for 30 minutes covered, uncover and bake for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, nuts, dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Add sugar, Pet milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cooking spray.
Stir well. Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and salt; cook for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine pineapple mixture and cream cheese; mix with whipped topping.
Mix everything together and chill.
Top with Mandarin oranges.

title: irish bread pudding
directions: Break eggs into large bowl, beat lightly.
Add milk and mix well.
Blend in sugar, vanilla and raisins.
Mix bread cubes into egg mixture until bread is well soaked.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 90 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mccoy's very famous salsa
directions: Finely dice onion, chili peppers, jalapeno peppers and garlic.
Saut all ingredients except tomatoes. Add tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes. Cool in refrigerator uncovered. Serve with chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour in casserole.
Top with chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken in a sack
directions: About 2 hours ahead, heat oven to 375°.
Rub paper bags, inside and outside, with oil.
Place a chicken inside each bag after covering the chicken with sauce and pouring some inside the cavity of each chicken.
Place the bags side by side in roasting pan or broiler pan.
Close ends of paper bags with wooden clothespin.
Cover roaster/broiler pan with lid or aluminum foil. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and flour.
Stir and add 3 tablespoons melted shortening.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut out; put in greased pan.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in large rectangular casserole dish.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: walnut cake
directions: Put all in a large bowl and mix.
Grease round pan and put in. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour; set oven to 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, peas, pimento, cheese and sauce in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash and potatoes
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat. Saute squash and potatoes until tender.

title: lemon rick
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add rice and mix; saute for about 3 minutes.
Add parsley, lemon juice and hot chicken stock mix and let simmer for 25 minutes.

title: apricot and walnut brown rice stuffing
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat until crisp.
Add rice, apricots, walnuts, raisins, parsley, thyme, salt, sage, pepper and chicken broth. Turn into 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stuffing may be baked inside poultry. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except dried beef into a ball.
Add dried beef around the ball.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a large kettle put all ingredients.
Mix together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Add apples and mix well.
Keep warm while filling jar with apples and then juice from cooking kettle.
Seal and process 20 minutes.
Quart jars.

title: tomato salad
directions: Chop vegetables. Add oil. Sprinkle with celery seed.

title: crab and shrimp quiche
directions: Mix crab and shrimp (rinsed and shredded) together and set aside.
Cook shallots in oleo in small saucepan until soft, 5 minutes.
Beat eggs with whisk; add milk, vermouth and hot sauce. Mix together.
Add crab and shrimp and additional milk to make 3 cups.
Pour into baked pie shell and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Ready to serve immediately.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute the onions with the salt pork and season with pepper until the onions are golden, but not dark.
Put the onion mixture into a saucepan and add the stock and thyme.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring on occasion.
Grate the cheese and add it to the soup after about 15 minutes of simmering.
Ten minutes before taking the soup off the heat, add a glass of wine or beer. Serve with croutons.
This is a quick soup that smells wonderful while it is simmering and is a way to use up ends of cheese and some wine or beer.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: pasta bolognese
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil until meat is done. Transfer to a pan.
Peel and chop onion; dice celery and carrot. Chop ham into small pieces.
Saute in remaining oil with onion, celery and carrot.
Add to ground meat.
Add water, tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper and thyme; cover and cook about 20 minutes. Add chicken broth; cook a few minutes more.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well.
Serve immediately with sauce.
